results.address: 1200 Hewitt Ave, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55104
results.raw: Man Fatally Shot by Homeowner at 1200 Hewitt Ave, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55104
results.rawLocation: 1200 Hewitt Ave, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55104
results.title: Man Fatally Shot by Homeowner

-Mz_JPvFL8nKXswlcejC.text: Incident reported at Griggs St & Hewitt Ave.

-Mz_JQ25jv2qj42S3oZk.text: The official Twitter page of the Saint Paul Police Department advises that officers are investigating a fatal shooting that occurred at 1:30 a.m. They have not yet released further details.

nib.text:
A man was fatally shot while trying break into a home in Saint Paul's Hamline-Midway neighborhood, police said.

The shooting was reported at about 1:30 a.m. at the house near Griggs Street and Hewitt Avenue.

Officers were informed that a man in his 30s kicked in the homeowner's front door, entered the home and threatened his daughter, "with whom the intruder had a relationship," a [police statement](https://www.facebook.com/sppdmn/posts/347187244121886?__cft__[0]=AZU2_Tmcg8H9s4-8DgYyiIT5yT8JOEcn8Zw9bMTOOI6-j0LUAPum6ENGptbe-oT3MNmy2c7phonTHAyVRvkU0RerIMTGAP2ZRQQc5ee-WB-O0Ym3aL-xqcYy9Bhi9TeUGOOiWm5EP61JcnWP7rpJZJqw&__tn__=%2CO%2CP-R) said.

Officers then located the man inside the home with multiple gunshot wounds. 

St. Paul Fire Department medics pronounced him dead at the scene.

The homeowner was questioned and released. 

The shooting is under investigation with Ramsey County officials, who will make a decision on charges.

The shooting is the 13th homicide of 2022 in  Saint Paul.
